 | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 7 March 2011}}</ref>\n\nHe works for [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen]] as a youth coach.\n\nCichon is of Polish origin.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{fussballdaten|cichonthomas|Thomas Cichon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cichon, Thomas}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Ruda \u015al\u0105ska]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:German people of Polish descent]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:1. FC K\u00f6ln players]]\n[[Category:1. FC K\u00f6ln II players]]\n[[Category:Rot-Wei\u00df Oberhausen players]]\n[[Category:Panionios F.C. players]]\n[[Category:VfL Osnabr\u00fcck players]]\n[[Category:Moroka Swallows F.C. players]]\n[[Category:German expatriate sportspeople in South Africa]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in South Africa]]\n\n\n{{Germany-footy-defender-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2011}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Thomas Cichon\n| fullname    = Thomas Cichon\n| image       = Cichon, Thomas OS 08-09 WP.JPG\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1976|07|09|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Ruda \u015al\u0105ska]], [[Poland]]\n| height      = {{convert|1.84|m|abbr=on}}\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen]] (youth)\n| clubnumber  = \n| youthyears1 = 1981\u20131985\n| youthclubs1 = [[BV Altenessen]]\n| youthyears2 = 1989\u20131990\n| youthclubs2 = Preu\u00dfen Essen\n| youthyears3 = 1990\u20131995\n| youthclubs3 = [[Schwarz-Wei\u00df Essen]]\n| years1      = 1995\u20132004\n| clubs1      = [[1. FC K\u00f6ln]]\n| caps1       = 211\n| goals1      = 8\n| years2      = 2004\u20132005\n| clubs2      = [[Rot-Wei\u00df Oberhausen]]\n| caps2       = 30\n| goals2      = 0\n| years3      = 2005\n| clubs3      = [[Panionios G.S.S.]]\n| caps3       = 6\n| goals3      = 0\n| years4      = 2006\u20132009\n| clubs4      = [[VfL Osnabr\u00fcck]]\n| caps4       = 98\n| goals4      = 16\n| years5      = 2009\u20132010\n| clubs5      = [[Moroka Swallows F.C.|Moroka Swallows]]\n| caps5       = 23\n| goals5      = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 1995\u20131998\n| nationalteam1  = [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U-21]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 20\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| manageryears1 = 2011\u2013\n| managerclubs1 = [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen]] (youth)\n}}\n\n'''Thomas Cichon''' ({{lang-pl|Tomasz Cicho\u0144}}; born 9 July 1976 in [[Ruda \u015al\u0105ska]]) is a [[Germany|German]] football manager and former [[Association football|football]] player.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/2bundesliga/vereine/2-bundesliga/2008-09/vfl-osnabrueck-45/432/spieler_thomas-cichon.html | title = Cichon, Thomas | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 7 March 2011}}</ref>\n\nHe is currently working for [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen]] as a youth coach.\n\nCichon is of Polish origin.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{fussballdaten|cichonthomas|Thomas Cichon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cichon, Thomas}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Ruda \u015al\u0105ska]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:German people of Polish descent]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:1. FC K\u00f6ln players]]\n[[Category:1. FC K\u00f6ln II players]]\n[[Category:Rot-Wei\u00df Oberhausen players]]\n[[Category:Panionios F.C. players]]\n[[Category:VfL